{'html': '&lt;p&gt;TOP SKILLS: &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong style="color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:12px;"&gt;1. Security/Cybersecurity PM experience and managing projects including $4-$5-million-dollar projects&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong style="color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:12px;"&gt;2. Know how to operate and use SAP, will be using SAP to process orders and manage budget (willing to flex on this and train a candidate- However, they need to be able to quickly learn a new application and demonstrate this)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong style="color:rgb(0,0,0);font-size:12px;"&gt;3. Working with Global Teams such as US, India, Spain, and Kentucky&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;- The SAP and cybersecurity levels should be intermediate doesn't need to be a expert in either area. Candidates should have worked on Cybersecurity projects &lt;span style="color:rgb(8,7,7);"&gt;&lt;span style="color:rgb(8,7,7);"&gt;beginning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; to end, and be able to enter transactions into SAP (&lt;strong&gt; will take a look at someone not versed in SAP but can be quick to pick up a new application) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;- Manage the full life cycle of multiple million-dollar cybersecurity projects using Microsoft Project&lt;p&gt;- Require &lt;span style="color:rgb(8,7,7);"&gt;&lt;span style="color:rgb(8,7,7);"&gt;senior&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;-level management and project management experience, with some cybersecurity experience&lt;p&gt;- Ability to work with various technologies like firewalls, infrastructure, and the industry&lt;p&gt;- Manage the global cybersecurity manufacturing efforts across 18 manufacturing sites (25% of time)&lt;p&gt;- Support other security projects within the organization (75% of time)&lt;p&gt;- Financial management experience (processing quotes, managing budgets, and communicating financial status)&lt;p&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;p&gt;•	Plan, initiate, and manage (IT) projects related to cybersecurity.&lt;p&gt;•	Lead and guide the work of technical staff and serve as a liaison between business and technical aspects of projects.&lt;p&gt;•	Develop project plans, goals, and budgets; identify resources needed, develop schedules and methods for measuring results.&lt;p&gt;•	Coordinate and oversee the implementation of new systems and procedures, ensuring adherence to best practices in cybersecurity.&lt;p&gt;•	Coordination work for Information security documentations including monthly metrics, status for leadership, SOW, contracts, MSAs. project data and status update in ServiceNow.&lt;p&gt;•	Work with various IT teams including PMO, legal, finance, communications, and other cross functional technical teams to meet Information security program objectives.&lt;p&gt;•	Onboard/offboard Information security vendors and service providers, support evaluating new security solutions POC and POV.&lt;p&gt;•	Support program management team to manage deadlines, budgets and activities for Information security projects and related activities.&lt;p&gt;•	Create Purchase Orders, Goods receipt in SAP system.&lt;p&gt;•	Work closely with stakeholders and business leaders to understand their needs and translate them into technical requirements.&lt;p&gt;•	Monitor progress of projects, making detailed plans to accomplish goals and directing the integration of technical activities.&lt;p&gt;•	Present and explain proposals, reports, and findings to clients and stakeholders.&lt;p&gt;•	Evaluate the organization's cybersecurity posture on an ongoing basis and recommend improvements as necessary.&lt;p&gt;•	Any other tasks assigned by the manager.&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;project management, cyber security, information security, budget management, stakeholder management, program management, sap, security, infrastructure&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Top Skills Details:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;project management,cyber security,information security,budget management,stakeholder management,program management,sap&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Skills &amp; Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;Desired Qualification&lt;p&gt;•	Degree in computer science, Cybersecurity, or a related field.&lt;p&gt;•	PMP or Prince 2 certified&lt;p&gt;•	Advanced degrees or certifications such as CISM, or CEH are a plus.&lt;p&gt;•	5+ years of experience in project management, in IT and cybersecurity.&lt;p&gt;•	Excellent problem-solving and leadership skills.&lt;p&gt;•	Strong communication skills to effectively convey complex security topics to both technical and non-technical staff.&lt;p&gt;•	Good understanding of the objectives of an Information security program.&lt;p&gt;•	Good knowledge of contract, SOW, MSA management.&lt;p&gt;•	Excellent working knowledge in MS Excel, PowerPoint, and Word with excellent communication and documentation skills.&lt;p&gt;•	Experience in operations budget, cost classification, purchase/order processes, invoicing.&lt;p&gt;•	Ability to work on site (Chicago) three days a week&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience Level:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;p&gt;Intermediate Level&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

